{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Crust","content":["Preheat a conventional oven to 325°F (see Tip). Lightly grease a springform pan (approx. 10 in. x 2½ in.) with butter, transfer pan to a baking sheet and set aside.","Place butter into mixing bowl and melt <nobr>3 min\/212°F\/speed <\/nobr>.  Add graham crackers, sugar and salt and mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix a further <nobr>5 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>.","Transfer crumb mixture into base of prepared springform pan. Press to form a firm compact layer. Transfer baking sheet with pan into oven and bake crust for 15 minutes (325°F). Set aside to cool. Meanwhile, wash and dry mixing bowl and increase oven temperature to 450°F."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Place cream cheese into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr> with aid of spatula. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix a further <nobr>30 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr> with aid of spatula.","Add sugar, sour cream, flour, lemon juice, vanilla and salt and mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr> with aid of spatula.","Without measuring cup, mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr> while adding eggs and egg yolks one at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix a further <nobr>30 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Pour cheesecake filling over prebaked crust. Let rest five minutes. Bake for 10 minutes (450°F), then reduce heat to 200°F and bake a further 1 hour and 45 minutes (200°F). Clean mixing bowl.","Turn off oven, crack open oven door and allow to cool slowly for one hour.","Run a thin knife around the edge of the pan to loosen cheesecake and allow to cool at room temperature (approx. 2 hr.). Refrigerate until fully set (approx. 4 hr. or overnight)."]},{"title":"Strawberry Topping","content":["Place strawberries, lemon juice and sugar into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>4 min\/140°F\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and refrigerate until chilled.","Just before serving, remove outer ring of springform pan. Pour Strawberry Topping over cheesecake, slice and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Crust","content":["3 oz unsalted butter, cubed, plus extra to grease","8 oz graham crackers, broken into pieces","1 tbsp sugar","&frac18; tsp salt"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["40 oz cream cheese, room temperature, cubed","9 oz sugar","3 oz sour cream","2 tbsp all-purpose flour","1 tsp lemon juice","1 tsp vanilla extract","&frac18; tsp salt","6 large eggs","2 egg yolks, from large eggs"]},{"title":"Strawberry Topping","content":["16 oz strawberries, stems removed, quartered","½ oz lemon juice","1 oz sugar"]}],"id":"r356249","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-f8u6XyDlC1s\/XZWYa8JwsWI\/AAAAAAAAd90\/qKjP1SCQ-nI0VYnngBmOE7j9AIJS211GQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_9NtxPbKyxDQbBQQ_.png","title":"New York Cheesecake","publishedAt":"2018-12-21T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"11 g","fat":"45 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"48 g","calories":"2628 kJ \/ 628 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sharp knife, springform pan (approx. 10 in. x 2½ in.), baking sheet, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Store leftover cheesecake in the refrigerator.","New York Cheesecakes bake optimally in a conventional oven. If using a convection oven, turn the fan off if your oven allows it, otherwise turn fan to lowest setting. All ovens heat differently however, so if using a convection oven it is recommended to reduce the temperature by 25°F-30°F and bake per conventional recipe time."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 30m","12 slices"]}